{
  "texts": [
    "After this evaluation, we run this process for all of the drug labels publicly available for each nation/region.",
    "By doing so, we construct additional databases with 108,958, 705,917, and 237,827 unique drug-ADE pairs from 1,048, 9,003, and 6,541 drug labels, with 929, 1,889, and 1,441 unique drug ingredient combinations and 3,570, 4,848, and 3,296 unique ADEs from European, British, and Japanese drug labels, respectively.",
    "Furthermore, by using international drug labels, we incorporate ADE data for an additional 1,777 unique drug ingredient combinations not found in OnSIDES.",
    "The database is presented in a format mirroring the OnSIDES database, and will be regularly updated simultaneously as part of the data repository.",
    "Given the complex architecture of BERT models, it is often difficult to interpret the results they output."
  ]
}